79 Come le pecorelle escon del chiuso 80 a una, a due, a tre, e l’altre stanno 81 timidette atterrando l’occhio e ’l muso;
82 e ciò che fa la prima, e l’altre fanno, 83 addossandosi a lei, s’ella s’arresta, 84 semplici e quete, e lo ’mperché non sanno;
85 sì vid’ io muovere a venir la testa 86 di quella mandra fortunata allotta, 87 pudica in faccia e ne l’andare onesta.

query.result:
79 As the sheep come out of the fold 80 one by one, two by two, and three by three, and the others stand 81 timidly, lowering their eyes and muzzles;
82 and what the first one does, the others do, 83 huddling up to her if she stops, 84 simple and quiet, and they do not know why;
85 thus I saw the head of that fortunate flock move to come, 86 modest in face and honest in gait.

94 "Without your asking, I confess to you
95 that this is a human body that you see;
96 that is why the light of the sun is broken on the ground.

109 When I had humbly denied
110 having ever seen him, he said: "Now look";
111 and he showed me a wound on his chest.

121 My sins were horrible;
122 but infinite goodness has such long arms,
123 that it embraces whoever turns to it.

